Function Reference/display space usage « WordPress Codex
-----------

Displays the amount of disk space used by a site.

Usage
-----

` <?php display_space_usage(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

none

Return
------

Outputs a preformatted string (see example)

Example
-------

The following are all examples of output when using
`display_space_usage()`:

    <strong>Used: 25% of 50MB</strong>

    <strong>Used: 15% of 2GB</strong>

(Note: The `<strong>` tags wrap the text displayed by
`display_space_usage()` and are not an error in the examples above)

Source File
-----------

`display_space_usage()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/ms.php`.

See also index of [Function
Reference](/Function_Reference "Function Reference") and index of
[Template Tags](/Template_Tags "Template Tags").

